{"author":{"id":"2b947bb98f783c65c2f134ada93c677f0a535e8a2bac5748d2bac91c3620a963"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1763410389,"nonce":"ZsMdX1PE0p8QgAQRAP1xKQnHwB8=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s7Yp-Ys","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7476","origin":"github"},"title":"Wrap HAL command-line tools for Galaxy","message":"HAL is a hierarchical alignment format used for pangenome and multiple-genome alignments. It stores alignments in a tree rather than a single linear reference, which avoids redundancy and handles rearrangements, duplications and indels more cleanly than formats like MAF. Each genome is aligned only to its parent, and all cross-genome relationships are derived from this structure. This makes it efficient for large comparative genomics and pangenome analyses.\n\nThe goal of this issue is to integrate the full HAL toolset into Galaxy so users can generate, inspect and query hierarchical genome alignments directly within the platform. You can find some more information [here](https://academic.oup.com/bioinformatics/article/29/10/1341/256598)\n\nThe HAL tools are already available through the cactus Bioconda package, so the work mainly involves wrapping them.\n \n---\nWrap the following tools for Galaxy \n- [ ] halStats\n- [ ] halValidate \n- [ ] hal2fasta \n- [ ] halExtract\n- [ ] hal2paf \n- [ ] hal2vg \n- [ ] maf2hal \n- [ ] hal2maf\n- [ ] halCoverage\n- [ ] halSummarizeMutations\n- [ ] halLodExtract\n- [ ] halLiftover\n- [ ] halWiggleLiftover\n- [ ] halSynteny\n- [ ] halAlignmentDepth\n- [ ] halSnps\n- [ ] halBranchMutations","files":null}]}